Pretoria - Two people were injured on Thursday, when a South African Police Service convoy collided with a pedestrian in Pretoria. "A motorbike, while leading a convoy out of Pretoria, collided with a pedestrian at the Fountains Circle. The pedestrian and the biker (a police officer) are reportedly injured and they have both been conveyed to a local hospital," spokesperson Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said. Naidoo said that there were no VIPs being conveyed in the convoy when the accident happened. African News Agency